Job Description

Perform on-site Indoor Air Quality inspection;

Conduct sampling and handle related tasks;

Training will be provided;

Perform any other ad hoc tasks assigned.

Requirements

Higher Diploma or above in any discipline;

Responsible, hardworking with positive working attitude;

1 year or more Indoor Air Quality experiences are advantages;

Fresh graduates with proactive attitude are also welcomed;

Immediately available is highly preferred;

Travel to China and Overseas is required;

Responsibilities

Participate in BioRadar related R&D projects;
Perform laboratory tests and data analysis independently by strictly following the standard operation procedures. Conduct experiments including nucleic acid extraction, PCR and quantitative PCR, isothermal amplification, DNA cloning, bacterial culture, bio-chip examination, etc.. Complete the research tasks assigned by supervisor;
Report experimental results, progressions and arising problems to supervisor routinely;
Carry out method development, optimization and validation under the supervision of R&D director;
Lab organizational duties such as sourcing of laboratory consumables, preparation of reagents and buffers, calibration and daily maintenance of laboratory instrumentation  related documentation.
Perform other duties as assigned.

Requirements

Higher Diploma  or above in molecular biology, microbiology, biochemistry, or other biotech-related disciplines;
Hands-on experience in basic  molecular bio-techniques including nucleic acid extraction and PCR
Mature, responsible, independent, career-minded and able to work under pressure;
Familiar with GLP or ISO regulations is a plus;Good command in both verbal and written Chinese and English
Relevant working experience preferred;

If you are passionate, driven and looking for a new and exciting opportunity within a successful and growing company, this may be the right role for you.

