Responsibilities:

Support the management of the new Clinical Translational Catalyst initiative which provides funding and regulatory support for biotech companies to catalyze the translation of their pipeline from pre-clinical to clinical stage;
Establish and maintain collaborative relationships with key stakeholders in the clinical translational path including Principal Investigators for Clinical Studies, Regulatory Professionals, Contract Research Organizations, Contract Manufacturing Organizations, and domain experts focusing in the fields of therapeutics and medical devices;
Implement and organize the overall administrative process for admission, assessment panel meeting and disbursement;
Promote the new HKSTP initiative within and outside of Hong Kong Science Park to attract qualified companies to participate in the initiative;
Interact with partner companies to understand their business/technical requirements and develop effective solutions;
Review and update Standard Operating Procedures, Programme Guide, protocols, flow charts, etc.;
Work collaboratively with other ITR teams and HKSTP organizational units; and
Perform any other duties as assigned by supervisors and management.

 Requirements:

Master degree in Pharmacology, Pharmaceutical Sciences, Pharmacy, Biomedical Sciences, Biochemistry, Biology, Biomedical Engineering and related clinical science or medicine disciplines;  A Clinical or PhD degree would be an advantage;
Minimum of 8 years of experience in R&D of therapeutics or medical devices with focus in IND or PMA regulatory submissions (e.g. FDA, NMPA), GMP manufacturing and QC/QA;
Experience in regulatory submission, clinical trial and marketing approval of small molecules, biologics, regenerative medicine, gene therapy or medical devices would be a plus;
Good analytical, interpersonal, presentation and communication skills;
Self-driven and work effectively in a highly collaborative environment;
Ability to manage up, down and across different functional teams will be crucial;
Proficient in MS office (Words, Excel and PowerPoint); and
Proficient in both written and spoken English and Chinese (Putonghua and Cantonese).
Candidate with higher qualification but less experience will also be considered.

[This position is open for referral by Recruitment agencies. The profile should be sent to our HR email address a g e n c y c v @ h k s t p . o r g ]

We offer market competitive compensation, 5-day work week and generous benefits including medical and life insurance.  To apply, please send your full resume with current and expected salary to the Human Resources & Office Administration Department, Hong Kong Science and Technology Parks Corporation, 5/F, Building 5E, 5 Science Park East Avenue, Hong Kong Science Park, Hong Kong or, by email on or before 27 January 2022. Please quote the reference number on the email subject/envelope and the application letter. 

