Responsibilities:

Build and maintain collaborative relationships with all stakeholders of the Institute for Translational Research (ITR) of HKSTP, including but not limited to academia, researchers, and business clients;
Provide instrumentation and application support to Biomedical Technology Support Centre (BSC);  
Assist users in operation and maintenance of laboratory instruments as well as support projects of BSC users;
Handle technical writing such as standard operating procedures, protocols, technical notes, guidelines and flow charts;
Understand customers’ technical requirements and develop effective solutions;
Provide overall administrative and procurement support; and
Perform any other duties as assigned by supervisors and management.

Requirements:

A bachelor’s degree or above in Biology, Biochemistry, Biotechnology, Biomedical Science, Microbiology, Pharmacology, or other discipline related to life science;
Minimum 2 years of relevant experience in life science or biomedical research laboratory; Less experience with higher qualification will also be considered;
A proven practical experience in operation of flow cytometer, sequencer or confocal microscopy would be preferred;
Keep abreast of the latest development in instrumentation and analytical methods;
Familiar with occupational hazards and standard safety practices;
Customer-centered service attitude with strong problem-solving skills is a must;
A good team player with excellent communication, analytical, interpersonal and presentation skills as well as able to work independently;
Proficient in MS office (Words, Excel and PowerPoint); and
Proficient in both written and spoken English and Chinese.

We offer market competitive compensation, 5-day work week, and generous benefits including medical and life insurance; and voluntary contribution in addition to the legal minimum MPF.  To apply, please send your full resume with current and expected salary to the Human Resources & Office Administration Department, Hong Kong Science and Technology Parks Corporation, 5/F, Building 5E, 5 Science Park East Avenue, Hong Kong Science Park, Hong Kong or, by email via "Apply Now" on or before 27 January 2022.   Please quote the reference number on the email subject/envelope and the application letter. 

