The Job

You will be expected to:

Perform In-house and On-site pipette calibrations, repairs, and maintenance in accordance with standard operation procedures;
Prepare calibration reports;
Carry out maintenance of laboratory equipment, inventory control, QC/QA procedures;
Manage spare parts and consumables, sourcing and purchasing as needed;
Support the Laboratory’s development, strategy planning and SOP setting;
Other ad-hoc duties assigned by the Laboratory Manager

The Candidate

You should have:


A higher diploma / associate degree / degree in science or engineering discipline;
1-2 years working experiences in a laboratory (less experienced applicant with good academic results will also be considered);
Basic understanding of HOKLAS / ISO 17025 requirements; measurement systems and metrology principles;
Fluent in English (both Oral and written) and Mandarin;
Proactive to learn and willing to pick up challenges;
Self-motivated, attention to details, problem-solving skills and good interpersonal skills.
