Position Summary:

The company is looking for several talented postdoctoral scientists. The ideal candidates must have extensive experience in molecular and cellular biology, cancer immunology, TCR T and CAR T-cell development, flow cytometry, and cell culture. Highly motivated and self-directed applicants interested in translational research in immuno-oncology are strongly encouraged to apply. However, applicants with related training and experience will be given priority.



Key Responsibilities include:

The positions are capable to lead, support the research activities and independently complete individual projects under the direction of CSO in the company. These positions will interact and collaborate with a number of scientists and associates highly trained in translational research of immuno-oncology. The persons will bring their skills, knowledge, and experience to be actively involved in the development of immunotherapies for a variety of cancers.


Basic education, experience and skills required for consideration:

A Ph.D. degree in life or biomedical sciences, or a related discipline is required, with 0-3 years of research experience;
A track record of publications in peer-reviewed scientific journals;
Solid knowledge in cancer immunology, molecular and cell biology, and biochemistry;
Experience in various genomic analytical platforms, such as NGS, RNA-sequencing, etc. is a plus;
Excellent communication skills (written and verbal in English and Chinese) with the ability to work independently and as part of a team;
Effectively lead a project in a translational research environment in order to successfully meet project goals;
Ability to perform and prioritize multiple simultaneous tasks;
Ability to design and execute experiments, critically interpret experimental results, and present data in a cogent and meaningful manner;
Ability to participate in the preparation of grant applications and publications.

Preferred experience and skills:

Experienced in gene cloning/re-engineering, antibody engineering, T cell-based therapy and CAR/TCR-T cell development is preferred;
Experience in handling mice, and PDX mouse models;
Experience in immunofluorescent staining, imaging/fluorescent microscopy, multi-parameter flow cytometry is preferred;

Salaries and Benefits
Salary and rank will be commensurate with qualifications and experience and the benefit are very competitive internationally.

Our company

You will be working within a company in Hong Kong Science and Technology Park. The company will recognize and reward you for your talent and commitment. If you have ability and desire to work among a community of professionals who will both challenge and develop your skill set, then we want to hear from you. Please submit your curriculum vitae, a statement detailing your research experience and skill, contact information (email address and phone number) and three professional references to Dr. Hua Zhang. For inquiry, Tel. (852) 56968321.

